\begin_layout Standard
In the analysis of single-subject fMRI datasets the primary task in a voxel-base
d analysis is to assign a level of significance at each voxel.
 This will depend on the estimation of both the magnitude of the response
 to the stimulus and the serial dependence of the time series, and especially
 on the assumptions made in that estimation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Various methods have been proposed in the literature to do this in both
 the time domain and frequency domain.
\end_layout

