\begin_layout Standard
By considering a periodic stimulus design in the frequency domain we found
 the analysis to be greatly simplified and at the same time provided insight
 into how non-periodic designs could be dealt with in a similar fashion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Trend Removal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Many voxel time series exhibit low frequency trend components.
 These may may be due to aliased high frequency physiological components
 or drifts in scanner sensitivity.
 Whatever the cause, these trends tend to vary non-linearly in time and
 may result in false positive activations if they are not accounted for
 in the model.
 We have found a simple running-lines smoother 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "vr:1999"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 to be a reliable method of trend removal (see Figure
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "trends"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 
\begin_inset Float figure
