\begin_layout Section
Conclusion and extensions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
Non-parametric spectral estimation is shown to be an accurate and self-calibrati
ng approach for analyzing periodic designs.
 The method makes few assumptions and is resistant to high-frequency artefacts
 whereas parametric time-domain approaches may be susceptible to these artefacts
 and biased by the assumptions they make on the form of the spectral density.
 The method can be easily extended to handle non-periodic event related
 designs and initial results are extremely promising.
 Non-parametric spectral estimation is shown to be an accurate and self-calibrat
ing approach for analyzing periodic designs.
\end_layout

